tps://web.archive.org/web/20160518025856/http://www.automobile-catalog.com/ Car specific accelerations]\n{{hidden end}}\n\n====Table of intercept values====\n{{hidden begin\n|toggle     = left\n|title      = Table of intercept vales\n|titlestyle = \n|bg1        = \n|bg2        = \n|ta1        = right\n|ta2        = left\n|extra1     = font-size:100%; padding-right:2.5em;\n|extra2     = font-size:120%; padding-left:3em;\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+'''Approach speeds of hazards which may foreseeably intercept the roadway'''\n|-\n! pedestrian(walk/run) !! bicycle !! cat !! dog !! deer !! elk\n|-\n| 3.1\u20135.6&nbsp;mph/27.78&nbsp;mph<ref name=Browning2006>{{cite journal |author=Browning, R. C. |author2=Baker, E. A. |author3=Herron, J. A. |author4=Kram, R.| title=Effects of obesity and sex on the energetic cost and preferred speed of walking |journal= Journal of Applied Physiology |volume= 100 |issue=2 |pages= 390\u2013398|year=2006 | doi=10.1152/japplphysiol.00767.2005 | pmid=16210434}}</ref> || 14.7f/s<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dot.ca.gov/hq/traffops/engineering/mutcd/ca_mutcd2014.htm |title=CAMUTCD |publisher=California Department of Transportation  |page=984 |quote=a bicyclist riding a bicycle 6 feet long to clear the last conflicting lane at a speed of 14.7 feet/sec }}</ref> || 29.8&nbsp;mph || 63.5&nbsp;km/h || 48.2&nbsp;km/h || 72.4&nbsp;km/h\n|}\n\nSee more [http://speedofanimals.com/ animal intercept speeds]. See article on [[Speed#Examples of different speeds|speed]].\n\n{{hidden end}}\n\n====Table of tire speed ratings====\n{{hidden begin\n|toggle     = left\n|title      = Table of tire speed ratings\n|titlestyle = \n|bg1        = \n|bg2        = \n|ta1        = right\n|ta2        = left\n|extra1     = font-size:100%; padding-right:2.5em;\n|extra2     = font-size:120%; padding-left:3em;\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+'''Tire speed rating<ref name=\"etrto.org\">{{cite web |url=http://www.etrto.org/files/files/ETRTO/Index_Publications_SM/SM_2010_GE