turalistic rear-end emergencies |journal=Accident Analysis & Prevention |volume=95 |issue=A |pages=209\u2013226 |date=October 2016 |url=http://eprints.whiterose.ac.uk/102162/1/A%20farewell%20to%20brake%20reaction%20times%20-%202016-06-23%20-%20for%20self-archiving.pdf |doi=10.1016/j.aap.2016.07.007 |pmid=27450793 |quote=The data show that drivers do not reliably respond to looming until it reaches .02 rad/sec}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The complete Catalog of Cars, car specs database |url=http://www.automobile-catalog.com/ |access-date=2015-12-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160518025856/http://www.automobile-catalog.com/ |archive-date=2016-05-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n! Speed [KM/H] !! Speed [MPH] !! Detection distance [m] !! Detection distance [ft] !! Time to collision [s]\n|-\n| ||5|| ||33\u201361||5\u20138\n|-\n| ||10|| ||47\u201387||3\u20136\n|-\n| ||15|| ||58\u2013106||3\u20135\n|-\n| ||20|| ||67\u2013123||2\u20134\n|-\n| ||25|| ||74\u2013137||2\u20134\n|-\n| ||30|| ||81\u2013150||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||35|| ||88\u2013162||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||40|| ||94\u2013173||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||45|| ||100\u2013184||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||50|| ||105\u2013194||1\u20133\n|-\n| ||55|| ||110\u2013203||1\u20133\n|-\n| ||60|| ||115\u2013212||1\u20132\n|-\n| ||65|| ||120\u2013221||1\u20132\n|-\n| ||70|| ||125\u2013229||1\u20132\n|-\n| ||75|| ||129\u2013237||1\u20132\n|-\n| ||80|| ||133\u2013245||1\u20132\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+'''Table of detection thresholds: looming motion of tractor-trailer  {{math|&theta;<sub>t</sub>{{=}}0.0397-0.0117, S{{=}}8ft}}'''<ref name=\"Hoffmann & Mortimer\"/><ref name=\"Maddox\"/><ref name=\"Markkula et al\"/>\n|-\n! Speed [KM/H] !! Speed [MPH] !! Detection distance [m] !! Detection distance [ft] !! Time to collision [s]\n|-\n| ||5|| ||38\u201371||5\u201310\n|-\n| ||10|| ||54\u2013100||4\u20137\n|-\n| ||15|| ||66\u2013123||3\u20136\n|-\n| ||20|| ||77\u2013142||3\u20135\n|-\n| ||25|| ||86\u2013158||2\u20134\n|-\n| ||30|| ||94\u2013173||2\u20134\n|-\n| ||35|| ||102\u2013187||2\u20134\n|-\n| ||40|| ||109\u2013200||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||45|| ||115\u2013212||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||50|| ||121\u2013224||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||55|| ||127\u2013235||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||60|| ||133\u2013245||2\u20133\n|-\n| ||65|| ||139\u2013255||1\u20133\n|-\n| ||70|| ||144\u2013265||1\u20133\n|-\n| ||75|| ||149\u2013274||1\u20132\n|-\n| ||80|| ||154\u2013283||1\u20132\n|}\n\nFor a person with SAVT limit of <math>\\dot\\theta_t</math>, the looming motion of a directly approaching object of size {{math|<var>S</var>}}, moving at velocity {{math|<var>v</var>}}, is not detectable until its distance {{math|<var>D</var>}} is<ref name=\"Weinberger\"/>\n:<math>D \\lessapprox \\sqrt{\\frac{S \\cdot v}{\\dot{\\theta_{t}}}-\\frac{S^2}{4}}</math>\n{{hidden end}}\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Advisory speed limit]]\n* [[Assumption of risk]]\n* [[Speed limit#Basic rule|Basic speed rule]]\n* [[Braking distance]]\n* [[Calculus of negligence]]\n* [[Duty of care]]\n* [[Geometric design of roads#Effects of insufficient sight distance|Effects of insufficient sight distance]]\n* [[Herbert William Heinrich|Heinrich's Law]]\n* [[Illusory superiority]]\n* [[International Regulations for Preventing Collisions at Sea#Section I .28Conduct of vessel in any condition of visibility.29|International Regulations for Preventing Collisions at Sea\u2014Part B, Section I, Rule 6: Safe speed]]\n* [[Road traffic safety]]\n* [[Standard of care]]\n* [[The man on the Clapham omnibus]]\n* [[Two-second rule]]\n* [[Visual flight rules]]\n* ''[[Volenti non fit injuria]]''\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist|30em|group=\"Note\"}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n===Further reading: tertiary sources===\n\n====ACDA related law reviews====\n*{{anchor|75_ALR3d_327}}{{cite book |title=American Law Reports--Annotated, 3rd Series |chapter=Automobiles: sudden emergency as exception to rule requiring motorist to maintain ability to stop within assured clear distance ahead |author=James O. Pearson |pub