{"title_page": "Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun", "text_new": "{{short description|2020 anime television series}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun\n| image           = Norimonoman kv.jpg\n| caption         = Anime key visual\n| ja_kanji        = \u306e\u308a\u3082\u306e\u307e\u3093 \u30e2\u30fc\u30d3\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u306e\u30ab\u30fc\u30af\u30f3\n| ja_romaji       = \n| genre           = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = \n| author          = \n| illustrator     = \n| publisher       = [[Shogakukan]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| demographic     = [[Comics]]\n| imprint         = \n| magazine        = Mebae\n| magazine_en     = \n| first           = April 1, 2020\n| last            = \n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Shinobu Sasaki\n| producer        = Taito It\u014d\n| writer          = Yoshimi Narita\n| music           = Cher Watanabe\n| studio          = [[CloverWorks]]\n| network         = [[NHK Educational TV|NHK-E]]\n| licensee        = \n| first           = April 2, 2020\n| last            = \n| episodes        = 1<!-- This parameter should only be incremented when new episodes air or when a [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources|reliable source]] can confirm a specific number of episodes. -->\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''''Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun'''''|\u306e\u308a\u3082\u306e\u307e\u3093 \u30e2\u30fc\u30d3\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u306e\u30ab\u30fc\u30af\u30f3}} is a multimedia kids project by [[Aniplex]] and [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan]]. A manga adaptation began serialization on [[Shogakukan]]'s ''Mebae'' magazine on April 1, 2020. An original [[anime]] television series produced by [[CloverWorks]] began airing on April 2, 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nCar-kun is a red [[sports car]] working as a delivery worker in the Mobile Land island. During his deliveries, he obeys traffic rules and meets all kinds of friends.\n\n==Characters==\n;{{nihongo|Car-kun|\u30ab\u30fc\u30af\u30f3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayahi Takagaki]]}}<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|url=https://norimonoman.com/character/|title=Character|website=norimonoman.com|language=Japanese|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n;{{nihongo|Ky\u016b-chan|\u30ad\u30e5\u30fc\u3061\u3083\u3093}}\n:{{voiced by|Yuka Maruyama}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Pappon|\u30d1\u30c3\u30dd\u30f3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Junji Majima]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Purin-chan|\u30d7\u30ea\u30f3\u3061\u3083\u3093}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Sakura Tange]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Pump|\u30dd\u30f3\u30d7}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nobuyuki Hiyama]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Daston|\u30c0\u30b9\u30c8\u30f3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Wasabi Mizuta]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Oyassan|\u304a\u3084\u3063\u3055\u3093}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Tessh\u014d Genda]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Sabibi|\u30b5\u30d3\u30d3\u30fc}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Show Hayami]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|DJ Navi|DJ\u30ca\u30d3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Setsuji Sat\u014d]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\nA manga adaptation began on [[Shogakukan]]'s ''Mebae'' magazine from April 1, 2020.<ref name=\"info\">{{cite web|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-03-03/sony-music-aniplex-produce-norimono-man-mobile-land-no-car-kun-kids-tv-anime/.157085|title=Sony Music, Aniplex Produce Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun Kids' TV|date=March 3, 2020|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Anime===\n[[Aniplex]] and [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan]] announced the TV series on March 3, 2020. It is directed by Shinobu Sasaki and produced by Taito It\u014d, with Toshiya Ono writing the scripts. Himu Ashitazu drafts the original character designs, with Hiromi Ogata adapting those character designs for animation. Cher Watanabe is composing the series' music, while Kisuke Koizumi is the sound director. The series is animated by [[CloverWorks]] and premieres on the [[NHK]]'s [[NHK Educational TV|education channel]] from April 2, 2020.<ref name=\"info\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://www.norimonoman.com/}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{CloverWorks}}\n\n[[Category:Anime with original screenplays]]\n[[Category:CloverWorks]]\n[[Category:NHK shows]]\n[[Category:Japanese children's television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 anime television series}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun\n| image           = Norimonoman kv.jpg\n| caption         = Anime key visual\n| ja_kanji        = \u306e\u308a\u3082\u306e\u307e\u3093 \u30e2\u30fc\u30d3\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u306e\u30ab\u30fc\u30af\u30f3\n| ja_romaji       = \n| genre           = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| title           = \n| author          = \n| illustrator     = \n| publisher       = [[Shogakukan]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| demographic     = [[Comics]]\n| imprint         = \n| magazine        = Mebae\n| magazine_en     = \n| first           = April 1, 2020\n| last            = \n| volumes         = \n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = TV series\n| director        = Shinobu Sasaki\n| producer        = Taito It\u014d\n| writer          = Yoshimi Narita\n| music           = Cher Watanabe\n| studio          = CloverWorks\n| network         = [[NHK Educational TV|NHK-E]]\n| licensee        = \n| first           = April 2, 2020\n| last            = \n| episodes        = 1<!-- This parameter should only be incremented when new episodes air or when a [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources|reliable source]] can confirm a specific number of episodes. -->\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''''Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun'''''|\u306e\u308a\u3082\u306e\u307e\u3093 \u30e2\u30fc\u30d3\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u306e\u30ab\u30fc\u30af\u30f3}} is a multimedia kids project by [[Aniplex]] and [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan]]. A manga adaptation began serialization on [[Shogakukan]]'s ''Mebae'' magazine on April 1, 2020. An original [[anime]] television series produced by [[CloverWorks]] began airing on April 2, 2020.\n\n==Plot==\nCar-kun is a red [[sports car]] working as a delivery worker in the Mobile Land island. During his deliveries, he obeys traffic rules and meets all kinds of friends.\n\n==Characters==\n;{{nihongo|Car-kun|\u30ab\u30fc\u30af\u30f3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Ayahi Takagaki]]}}<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web|url=https://norimonoman.com/character/|title=Character|website=norimonoman.com|language=Japanese|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n;{{nihongo|Ky\u016b-chan|\u30ad\u30e5\u30fc\u3061\u3083\u3093}}\n:{{voiced by|Yuka Maruyama}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Pappon|\u30d1\u30c3\u30dd\u30f3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Junji Majima]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Purin-chan|\u30d7\u30ea\u30f3\u3061\u3083\u3093}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Sakura Tange]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Pump|\u30dd\u30f3\u30d7}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Nobuyuki Hiyama]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Daston|\u30c0\u30b9\u30c8\u30f3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Wasabi Mizuta]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Oyassan|\u304a\u3084\u3063\u3055\u3093}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Tessh\u014d Genda]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|Sabibi|\u30b5\u30d3\u30d3\u30fc}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Show Hayami]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{nihongo|DJ Navi|DJ\u30ca\u30d3}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Setsuji Sat\u014d]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\nA manga adaptation began on [[Shogakukan]]'s ''Mebae'' magazine from April 1, 2020.<ref name=\"info\">{{cite web|first=Rafael|last=Antonio Pineda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-03-03/sony-music-aniplex-produce-norimono-man-mobile-land-no-car-kun-kids-tv-anime/.157085|title=Sony Music, Aniplex Produce Norimono Man Mobile Land no Car-kun Kids' TV|date=March 3, 2020|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Anime===\n[[Aniplex]] and [[Sony Music Entertainment Japan]] announced the TV series on March 3, 2020. It is directed by Shinobu Sasaki and produced by Taito It\u014d, with Toshiya Ono writing the scripts. Himu Ashitazu drafts the original character designs, with Hiromi Ogata adapting those character designs for animation. Cher Watanabe is composing the series' music, while Kisuke Koizumi is the sound director. The series is animated by [[CloverWorks]] and premieres on the [[NHK]]'s [[NHK Educational TV|education channel]] from April 2, 2020.<ref name=\"info\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://www.norimonoman.com/}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{CloverWorks}}\n\n[[Category:Anime with original screenplays]]\n[[Category:CloverWorks]]\n[[Category:NHK shows]]\n[[Category:Japanese children's television series]]\n", "name_user": "Unnamelessness", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norimono_Man_Mobile_Land_no_Car-kun"}
{"title_page": "Find My Way", "text_new": "{{Short description|2020 single by DaBaby}}\n{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Find My Way\n| type       = single\n| cover      = DaBaby - Find My Way.png\n| alt        =\n| artist     = [[DaBaby]]\n| album      = \n| released   = April 1, 2020\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 2:19\n| label      = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| writer     =\n* [[DaBaby|Jonathan Kirk]]\n* De'Juane Dunwood\n| producer   = DJ Kid\n| prev_title = [[Vibez]]\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|gmK_gaE5v9A|\"Find My Way\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Find My Way'''\" (stylized in [[all caps]]) is a song by American rapper [[DaBaby]], released as the second single from his upcoming third studio album on April 1, 2020.\n\n==Background==\nThe song talks about DaBaby being able to find the way to his career.\n\nThe song is produced by DJ K.i.D, who also produced DaBaby's \"[[Intro (DaBaby song)|Intro]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/the-making-of-dababys-intro-with-dj-k-i-d|title=The Making Of DaBaby's \"INTRO\" With DJ K.i.D|work=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Thioubou|first=Ndeye|date=December 19, 2019|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}</ref> and \"[[Shut Up (DaBaby song)|Shut Up]]\".\n\nDaBaby switches the flow and cadence on the song and sings on the chorus, while rapping on the two verses.\n\n==Promotion==\nDaBaby teased the song for the first time with a video posted on Instagram on March 25, 2020. He later posted an acoustic video with guitarist Einer Bankz on March 30. The track was released with the music video on April 1, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dababy-shares-video-for-new-song-find-my-way-watch/|title=DaBaby Shares Video for New Song \"Find My Way\": Watch|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Strauss|first=Matthew|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video, directed by Reel Goats, was released on April 1, 2020, and co-stars Instagram influencer B. Simone. The concept bears similarities to the story of [[Bonnie and Clyde]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9348392/dababy-find-my-way-video|title=DaBaby's 'Find My Way' Video Tells a Tragic 'Bonnie & Clyde'-Inspired Tale: Watch|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> It shows DaBaby with B. Simone in a car, with flashbacks of the pair shooting people. They then check into in a hotel. Other patrons soon tell the hotel about them and the hotel staff knocks on DaBaby and Simone's hotel door and tells them to get out. DaBaby and Simone do not talk, but Simone finds the gun and gives it to DaBaby. The hotel staff start shooting down the room to get in and DaBaby, who is hidden, begins returning fire.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/dababy-find-my-way-video|title=Watch DaBaby's Short Film for New Song \"Find My Way\"|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DaBaby}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:DaBaby songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by DaBaby]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2020 single by DaBaby}}\n{{refimprove|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Find My Way\n| type       = single\n| cover      = DaBaby - Find My Way.png\n| alt        =\n| artist     = [[DaBaby]]\n| album      = \n| released   = April 1, 2020\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 2:19\n| label      = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| writer     =\n* [[DaBaby|Jonathan Kirk]]\n* De'Juane Dunwood\n| producer   = DJ Kid\n| prev_title = [[Vibez]]\n| prev_year  = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|gmK_gaE5v9A|\"Find My Way\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Find My Way'''\" (stylized in [[all caps]]) is a song by American rapper [[DaBaby]], released as the second single from his upcoming third studio album on April 1, 2020.\n\n==Background==\nThe song talks about DaBaby being able to find the way to his career.\n\nThe song is produced by DJ K.i.D, who also produced DaBaby's \"[[Intro (DaBaby song)|Intro]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://genius.com/a/the-making-of-dababys-intro-with-dj-k-i-d|title=The Making Of DaBaby's \"INTRO\" With DJ K.i.D|work=[[Genius (website)|Genius]]|last=Thioubou|first=Ndeye|date=December 19, 2019|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}</ref> and \"[[Shut Up (DaBaby song)|Shut Up]]\".\n\nDaBaby switches the flow and cadence on the song and sings on the chorus, while rapping on the two verses.\n\n==Promotion==\nDaBaby teased the song for the first time with a video posted on Instagram on March 25, 2020. He later posted an acoustic video with guitarist Einer Bankz on March 30. The track was released with the music video on April 1, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dababy-shares-video-for-new-song-find-my-way-watch/|title=DaBaby Shares Video for New Song \"Find My Way\": Watch|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Strauss|first=Matthew|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was released on April 1, 2020, and was directed by Reel Goats. The concept bears similarities to the story of [[Bonnie and Clyde]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9348392/dababy-find-my-way-video|title=DaBaby's 'Find My Way' Video Tells a Tragic 'Bonnie & Clyde'-Inspired Tale: Watch|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> It shows DaBaby with B. Simone in a car, with flashbacks of the pair shooting people. They then check into in a hotel. Other patrons soon tell the hotel about them and the hotel staff knocks on DaBaby and Simone's hotel door and tells them to get out. DaBaby and Simone do not talk, but Simone finds the gun and gives it to DaBaby. The hotel staff start shooting down the room to get in and DaBaby, who is hidden, begins returning fire.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/04/dababy-find-my-way-video|title=Watch DaBaby's Short Film for New Song \"Find My Way\"|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DaBaby}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:DaBaby songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by DaBaby]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records singles]]\n", "name_user": "Ss112", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMusic video", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Find_My_Way"}
{"title_page": "Jenny Mikakos", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix= [[The Honourable]]\n| name            = Jenny Mikakos\n| nationality     = Australian\n| honorific-suffix= [[Victorian Legislative Council|MLC]]\n| image           = Cabinet 2018-160L.jpg\n| image_upright   = 1.15\n| caption = Mikakos (left), with Governor of Victoria Linda Dessau\n| office          = Member of the [[Victorian Legislative Council]] for [[Northern Metropolitan Region]]\n| term_start      = 18 September 1999\n| portfolio       = Minister for Health, \nMinister for Ambulance Services, Minister for the Coordination of Health and Human Services - COVID-19\n| predecessor     =\n| successor       =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1969|1|25}}\n| birth_place     =\n| death_date      =\n| death_place     =\n| party           = [[Australian Labor Party (Victorian Branch)|Labor Party]]\n| spouse          =\n| profession      =\n| signature       =\n| footnotes       =\n|}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=June 2014}}\n'''Jenny Mikakos''' (born 25 January 1969) is an Australian politician for the [[Australian Labor Party (Victorian Branch)|Labor Party]]. She is currently the Minister for Health, Minister for Ambulance Services, Minister for the Coordination of Health and Human Services COVID-19 and the Deputy Leader of the Government in [[Members of the Victorian Legislative Council, 2006-2010|Member of the Legislative Council]] for [[Northern Metropolitan Region]].<ref name=\"Mikakos\">{{cite encyclopedia| editor = Suzannah Pearce| encyclopedia = Who's Who in Australia Live!| title = MIKAKOS Jenny| date = 2006-11-17| publisher = Crown Content Pty Ltd| location = North Melbourne, Vic}}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n\nMikakos was first elected as the Member for Jika Jika Province in the State of [[Victoria, Australia|Victoria]] in September 1999.{{ref|JikaJika}} From 1999 until 2006, she represented the [[Legislative Council]] province of [[Jika Jika, Victoria|Jika Jika]].<ref name=\"Mikakos\"/> Mikakos' electorate was abolished at the [[2006 Victorian state election|2006 election]] as part of major reforms of the Legislative Council introduced after the 2002 election, but she won the second position on the Labor ticket for the replacement electorate, the larger, five-member Northern Metropolitan Region. She was first on the Labor ticket at the 2010, 2014 and 2018 election.\n\nFrom 2002 until 2007, she was appointed Parliamentary Secretary for Justice. From 2007 until 2010 she was appointed Parliamentary Secretary for Planning.\n\nFrom 2010 until 2014 she was the Shadow Minister for Community Services, Children, Youth Affairs, Youth Justice and Seniors and Ageing.\n\nFrom 2014 until 2018, she was appointed Minister for Families and Children, Early Childhood Education and Youth Affairs in the Andrews Labor Government.\n\nIn November 2018, Mikakos was appointed the Minister for Health and Minister for Ambulance Services following the re-election of the Andrews Labor Government.\n\nIn March 2020, she was appointed Deputy Leader of the Government in the Legislative Council.\n\nIn April 2020, Mikakos was appointed as the Minister for the Coordination of Health and Human Services COVID-19 as part of the Victorian Government's response to the coronavirus global pandemic.\n\nIn Parliament, Mikakos voted against the human cloning  bill but for stem cell research, for abortion decriminalisation, for assisted reproductive technology reforms and for dying with dignity laws. These bills were subject to a conscience votes in the Labor Party.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nJenny Mikakos was the first woman of Greek descent elected to an Australian Parliament. She grew up in Northcote, in her electorate, to a migrant working-class family.\n\nShe attended [[Ivanhoe Girls' Grammar School]], Thornbury High School,<ref name=\"Mikakos\"/> and the [[University of Melbourne]] where she obtained arts and law degrees. Before her election to Parliament, Mikakos worked as a commercial and tax lawyer for [[King & Wood Mallesons]] and  Jerrard & Stuk. She was briefly a Councillor with the City of Northcote in the early 1990s.{{ref|career}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n#{{note|left}} Austin, P., [http://www.theage.com.au/news/national/alp-heavies-tackle-faction-fracas-before-poll/2006/02/26/1140888749262.html ALP heavies tackle faction fracas before poll], ''The Age'', 27 February 2006\n#{{note|SocialistLeft}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060427003109/http://www.crikey.com.au/articles/2002/06/16-deliajune19.html With Crikey's Delia Delegate, all the ALP dirty laundry is on the table], 16 June 2002\n#{{note|hard-left}} Carney, S., [http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2002/06/17/1023864403072.html Labor supremos back new alliance], ''The Age'', 18 June 2002\n#{{note|career}} [http://www.parliament.vic.gov.au/handbook/preview_main.cfm?menuid=3&listtype=report&listid=12 Parliamentary handbook]\n#{{note|JikaJika}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060302060455/http://home.vicnet.net.au/~jmikakos/ Jenny Mikakos MP Member for Jika Jika Province]\n#{{note|AJF}} [http://www.gamblingresearch.org.au/__ca2569020010922a.nsf/Print/d2414d006c362bfdca256e9b00092112?OpenDocument&Click= Jenny Mikakos, Chair of the Aboriginal Justice Forum]{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n#{{note|GLBT}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060302060455/http://home.vicnet.net.au/~jmikakos/ Jenny Mikakos MP Member for Jika Jika Province]\n#{{note|WCSAC}} [http://www.justice.vic.gov.au/CA256902000FE154/Lookup/DOJ_CORRECTIONS_PART3/$file/Better_Pathways_Strategy.pdf Women\u2019s Correctional Services Advisory Committee]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060629145052/http://147.202.41.181/discover/news/documents/ALSONewsJan06.pdf Celebrating 25 years of the Alternative Life Styles Organisation (ALSO)]\n* [http://www.evolutionpublishing.com.au/mcv/index2.php?option=com_content&do_pdf